revisions.description: Add cadMcastForwardDestIfType as an index of cadMcastForwardDestEntry.
Add cadMcastIgmpThrottleEnable, cadMcastIgmpThrottleBurstSize, cadMcastIgmpThrottleInterval and cadMcastIgmpThrottleIncrement for US IGMP Throttling.
Change cadMcastStatsTunnelIndex from not-accessible to read-only

Remove 120 seconds from cadStaticFqdnCachePollInterval. Add cadMcastForwardUseDefaultFlow object. Reduce the size of cadFqdnCacheName, cadDsgIfSrcName and cadMgmdPmStaticGroupSourceName from 250 to 154.
Rename cadStaticFqdnCfgGroup to cadFqdnCfgGroup. Rename cadStaticFqdnCacheEntry to cadFqdnCacheEntry. Change SYNTAX of FQDN name from OCTET STRING to SnmpAdminString.
Change range of cadStaticFqdnCachePollInterval from (1800..2678400) to (300..86400)

Remove cadMgmdPmStaticGroupName, cadMgmdPmStaticGroupSourceStaticIpAddr and cadDsgIfDestName. Rename cadMgmdPmStaticGroupStaticIpAddr to Rename cadMgmdPmStaticGroup. Add cadStaticFqdnCacheStatus. Change FQDN name maximum size from 256 to 250.
Add cadStaticFqdnCfgGroup, cadStaticFqdnCacheEntry, cadDsgIfClassifierCfgEntry, and cadMgmdPmStaticGroupCfgEntry.

cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingTable.name: cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingTable
cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingTable.description: The list of static multicast MAC/IP bindings. Bindings in this table are used to override the standard RFC bindings.

cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingEntry.name: cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingEntry
cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingTable.

cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingAddressType.name: cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingAddressType
cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingAddressType.description: The address type of the InetAddress variables in this table.

cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingMacAddress.name: cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingMacAddress
cadMcastStaticMacIpBindingMacAddress.description: The MAC address to bind to the multicast group address in the ARP table.

cadMcastMrouteTable.name: cadMcastMrouteTable
cadMcastMrouteTable.description: The list of static mroutes. Routes in this table are used to override unicast routes.

cadMcastMrouteEntry.name: cadMcastMrouteEntry
cadMcastMrouteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cadMcastMrouteTable.

cadMcastMrouteType.name: cadMcastMrouteType
cadMcastMrouteType.description: The address type of the InetAddress variables in this table.

cadMcastMrouteSourcePrefix.name: cadMcastMrouteSourcePrefix
cadMcastMrouteSourcePrefix.description: The multicast route source network prefix.

cadMcastMrouteRpfAddress.name: cadMcastMrouteRpfAddress
cadMcastMrouteRpfAddress.description: The multicast route RPF neighbor address.

cadMcastForwardEntry.name: cadMcastForwardEntry
cadMcastForwardEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cadMcastForwardTable.

cadMcastForwardAddressType.name: cadMcastForwardAddressType
cadMcastForwardAddressType.description: The address type of the InetAddress variables in this table.

cadMcastForwardSourceAddress.name: cadMcastForwardSourceAddress
cadMcastForwardSourceAddress.description: The multicast source address or 0 for all sources.

cadMcastForwardSourceIf.name: cadMcastForwardSourceIf
cadMcastForwardSourceIf.description: The multicast source interface or 0 for all interface.

cadMcastForwardDestIfList.name: cadMcastForwardDestIfList
cadMcastForwardDestIfList.description: The index id of the list of destination interfaces.

cadMcastForwardCount.name: cadMcastForwardCount
cadMcastForwardCount.description: The number of multicast packets forwarded for this group.

cadMcastForwardDestTable.name: cadMcastForwardDestTable
cadMcastForwardDestTable.description: The list of multicast forwarding destination interfaces.

cadMcastForwardDestEntry.name: cadMcastForwardDestEntry
cadMcastForwardDestEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cadMcastForwardDestTable.

cadMcastForwardDestIfListId.name: cadMcastForwardDestIfListId
cadMcastForwardDestIfListId.description: The index id of the list of destination interfaces.

cadMcastForwardDestIf.name: cadMcastForwardDestIf
cadMcastForwardDestIf.description: The multicast dest interface.For the case of cadMcastForwardDestIfType being set to sdv(2), the destination interface will be a DCAM slot number. For all other settings of cadMcastForwardDestIfType, the destination interface will be an ifIndex.

cadMcastForwardDestIfType.name: cadMcastForwardDestIfType
cadMcastForwardDestIfType.description: The type of multicast destination interface.

cadMcastClearForwardCounts.name: cadMcastClearForwardCounts
cadMcastClearForwardCounts.description: This variable always returns false upon reading. When set to true, the multicast forward counts are cleared.

cadMcastForwardUseDefaultFlow.name: cadMcastForwardUseDefaultFlow
cadMcastForwardUseDefaultFlow.description: When set to true, the forwarding of multicast data packets uses the default flow

cadMcastDeleteDsg.name: cadMcastDeleteDsg
cadMcastDeleteDsg.description: This variable always returns false(2) upon reading. When set to true(1), all rows in every DSG MIB table are deleted. except dsgIfDownstreamEntry(s) are reset to default values.

cadMcastIgmpThrottleBurstSize.name: cadMcastIgmpThrottleBurstSize
cadMcastIgmpThrottleBurstSize.description: Maximum size of IGMP throttle bucket per MAC address.

cadMcastIgmpThrottleInterval.name: cadMcastIgmpThrottleInterval
cadMcastIgmpThrottleInterval.description: Interval in seconds between replenishing an IGMP throttle bucket.

cadMcastIgmpThrottleIncrement.name: cadMcastIgmpThrottleIncrement
cadMcastIgmpThrottleIncrement.description: Number of tokens added to a throttle bucket every cadMcastIgmpThrottleInterval seconds.

cadMcastClearVideoForwardCounts.name: cadMcastClearVideoForwardCounts
cadMcastClearVideoForwardCounts.description: This variable always returns false upon reading. When set to true, the SDV multicast forward counts (i.e. cadMcastForwardCount attribute of the rows of cadMcastForwardEntry for IEQ video) are cleared.

cadFqdnCacheEnable.name: cadFqdnCacheEnable
cadFqdnCacheEnable.description: If set to true(1), polling for the C4 applications' FQDN / IP cache binding updates will be enabled. If set to false(2), no polling will be performed.

cadFqdnCachePollInterval.name: cadFqdnCachePollInterval
cadFqdnCachePollInterval.description: Poll interval in seconds for checking for updates to the C4 application's FQDN/IP cache binding.

cadFqdnCacheRefresh.name: cadFqdnCacheRefresh
cadFqdnCacheRefresh.description: This variable always returns false(2) upon reading. When set to true(1), the C4 application will immediatelly poll the DNS resovler for an update of each of the FQDN IP bindings contained in the cadStaticFqdnCacheTable.

cadFqdnCacheTable.name: cadFqdnCacheTable
cadFqdnCacheTable.description: The list of the FQDN IP bindings from DNS resolver.

cadFqdnCacheEntry.name: cadFqdnCacheEntry
cadFqdnCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cadFqdnCacheTable.

cadFqdnCacheName.name: cadFqdnCacheName
cadFqdnCacheName.description: The name can be a host name or fully/partially qualified domain name.

cadFqdnCacheFqdn.name: cadFqdnCacheFqdn
cadFqdnCacheFqdn.description: the fully qualified domain name returned from DNS resolver.

cadFqdnCacheIpAddrType.name: cadFqdnCacheIpAddrType
cadFqdnCacheIpAddrType.description: The IP address type associated with the IP address. If the IP address is zero length, this object will be set to unknown(0).

cadFqdnCacheIpAddress.name: cadFqdnCacheIpAddress
cadFqdnCacheIpAddress.description: The IP address type associated with the resolved IP address. This object is set to zero length, if the resolved IP address is not found.

cadFqdnCacheLastUpdateTime.name: cadFqdnCacheLastUpdateTime
cadFqdnCacheLastUpdateTime.description: The sysUpTime when a cadStaticFqdnCacheEntry is updated.

cadFqdnCacheStatus.name: cadFqdnCacheStatus
cadFqdnCacheStatus.description: validIp(1) - found a valid IP address associated with cadStaticFqdnCacheName. unknownIp(2) - DNS server does not have the IP address. invalidIp(3) - IP address returned by the service is not a vlid unicast IP address. timeout(4) - DNS resolver send request but get timeout. genError(5) - general error.

cadDsgIfClassifierCfgTable.name: cadDsgIfClassifierCfgTable
cadDsgIfClassifierCfgTable.description: The list of the FQDN IP bindings from DNS resolver.

cadDsgIfClassifierCfgEntry.name: cadDsgIfClassifierCfgEntry
cadDsgIfClassifierCfgEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cadDsgIfClassifierCfgTable.

cadDsgIfSrcName.name: cadDsgIfSrcName
cadDsgIfSrcName.description: The source name where a source name can be a host name, partially, or fully qualified domain name.

cadMgmdPmStaticGroupCfgTable.name: cadMgmdPmStaticGroupCfgTable
cadMgmdPmStaticGroupCfgTable.description: The list of the FQDN IP bindings from DNS resolver.

cadMgmdPmStaticGroupCfgEntry.name: cadMgmdPmStaticGroupCfgEntry
cadMgmdPmStaticGroupCfgEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cadMgmdPmStaticGroupCfgTable.

cadMgmdPmStaticGroupAddress.name: cadMgmdPmStaticGroupAddress
cadMgmdPmStaticGroupAddress.description: the static IP address of the group.

cadMgmdPmStaticGroupSourceName.name: cadMgmdPmStaticGroupSourceName
cadMgmdPmStaticGroupSourceName.description: Group source name can be a host name or fully/partially qualified domain name.

cadMcastStatsTable.name: cadMcastStatsTable
cadMcastStatsTable.description: The Cadent Multicast Stats Table contains the packet and byte counters for an instance of a multicast stream. If the multicast stream is for a DSG tunnel, it also contains the ifIndex of the channel carrying the tunnel and the tunnel number.

cadMcastStatsEntry.name: cadMcastStatsEntry
cadMcastStatsEntry.description: An entry in the Cadent Multicast Stats Table. An entry in this table exists for each active multicast service flow when MDF is enabled on the cable-mac.

cadMcastStatsDsid.name: cadMcastStatsDsid
cadMcastStatsDsid.description: This object contains the DSID value with which the CMTS labels the DSG Tunnel traffic.

cadMcastStatsSentPkts.name: cadMcastStatsSentPkts
cadMcastStatsSentPkts.description: This attribute indicates the count of the number of packets transmitted for this outgoing multicast stream.

cadMcastStatsSentOctets.name: cadMcastStatsSentOctets
cadMcastStatsSentOctets.description: This attribute indicates the count of the number of octets transmitted for this outgoing multicast stream.

cadMcastStatsDroppedPkts.name: cadMcastStatsDroppedPkts
cadMcastStatsDroppedPkts.description: This attribute indicates the count of the number of packets dropped for this outgoing multicast stream.

cadMcastStatsDroppedOctets.name: cadMcastStatsDroppedOctets
cadMcastStatsDroppedOctets.description: This attribute indicates the count of the number of octets dropped for this outgoing multicast stream.

cadMcastStatsDsIfIndex.name: cadMcastStatsDsIfIndex
cadMcastStatsDsIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the downstream channel carrying this stream. Zero if stream is not for DSG.

cadMcastStatsTunnelIndex.name: cadMcastStatsTunnelIndex
cadMcastStatsTunnelIndex.description: The index into the DSG Tunnel table that represent a tunnel. Zero if stream is not for DSG.

cadMcastStatsDsChSetId.name: cadMcastStatsDsChSetId
cadMcastStatsDsChSetId.description: This attribute provides the reference for the Downstream Channel Set within a MAC Domain that the multicast Servide flow is replicated to.

cadMcastStatsGSFID.name: cadMcastStatsGSFID
cadMcastStatsGSFID.description: This attribute indicates the identifier assigned to the multicast group service flow.

cadDsgIfTunnelChToGroupTable.name: cadDsgIfTunnelChToGroupTable
cadDsgIfTunnelChToGroupTable.description: The list of entries of DSG tunnel channel to group.

cadDsgIfTunnelChToGroupEntry.name: cadDsgIfTunnelChToGroupEntry
cadDsgIfTunnelChToGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cadDsgIfTunnelChToGroupTable.

cadDsgIfTunnelGrpIndex.name: cadDsgIfTunnelGrpIndex
cadDsgIfTunnelGrpIndex.description: This attribute indicates DSG tunnel group index.
